Frederick Morris (27 August 1893 – 4 July 1962) was an English professional footballer who played as an inside-left forward.
Morris was born in Tipton, Staffordshire. He was top scorer with 37 goals in Division One in West Bromwich Albion's League Championship-winning season of 1919–20.He died in Tipton, aged 68.
